00:38:54,080 --> 00:38:56,420
you didn't want anything.

1406
00:38:56,420 --> 00:38:57,300
(Sudden duet)

1407
00:38:57,600 --> 00:38:59,000
You just wanted An Er dead.

1408
00:38:59,280 --> 00:38:59,680
Look.

1409
00:38:59,680 --> 00:39:01,320
Look at her killer reaction.

1410
00:39:01,320 --> 00:39:02,100
(Perfect chance to review)

1411
00:39:03,040 --> 00:39:03,960
Watching it yourself is one thing.

1412
00:39:03,960 --> 00:39:05,200
(Taking center stage)
You even remind others to watch.

1413
00:39:05,200 --> 00:39:07,080
(Sharing rank-up tips)

1414
00:39:07,080 --> 00:39:08,040
(Jin Xiangyu's hidden secret)
Look.

1415
00:39:08,520 --> 00:39:09,640
I went back to my room that day

1416
00:39:09,640 --> 00:39:12,160
and realized that things had
been moved around and put back.

1417
00:39:12,440 --> 00:39:13,680
So I asked Pai

1418
00:39:13,680 --> 00:39:15,360
what on earth happened.

1419
00:39:15,360 --> 00:39:16,320
She told me

1420
00:39:16,320 --> 00:39:19,000
that An Er was acting
all sketchy in my room.

1421
00:39:19,640 --> 00:39:20,520
So,

1422
00:39:20,880 --> 00:39:22,600
I started keeping a close eye on him.

1423
00:39:22,600 --> 00:39:24,640
I noticed An Er had collected

1424
00:39:24,640 --> 00:39:27,600
some of my son's and Master's hair

1425
00:39:27,600 --> 00:39:29,440
to send in for a DNA test.

1426
00:39:31,480 --> 00:39:33,280
I wanted to intercept that report

1427
00:39:33,280 --> 00:39:33,960
because I thought

1428
00:39:33,960 --> 00:39:35,840
(Jin Xiangyu's hidden secret)
my son was definitely Master's.

1429
00:39:35,840 --> 00:39:37,880
But the report told me...

1430
00:39:38,300 --> 00:39:39,020
(DNA Test Report)

1431
00:39:39,030 --> 00:39:39,700
(Not biologically related.)

1432
00:39:39,700 --> 00:39:41,220
If I see anything in here

1433
00:39:41,220 --> 00:39:42,980
related to laser pointers or mirrors,

1434
00:39:42,980 --> 00:39:44,500
I'm locking in the killer.

1435
00:39:47,060 --> 00:39:48,160
But Pai can also get into our room.

1436
00:39:48,200 --> 00:39:49,040
You're panicking.

1437
00:39:49,040 --> 00:39:49,760
I only noticed now.

1438
00:39:49,760 --> 00:39:50,380
Xiaoding, well said.

1439
00:39:50,400 --> 00:39:51,560
You've got a point there.

1440
00:39:51,560 --> 00:39:53,200
My good boy.

1441
00:39:53,260 --> 00:39:55,060
(The defensive son)

1442
00:39:55,360 --> 00:39:56,760
You called her
your sweetheart yesterday,

1443
00:39:56,760 --> 00:39:58,160
and today you're calling her a killer.

1444
00:39:59,440 --> 00:40:00,440
He called her...

1445
00:40:00,440 --> 00:40:01,600
(She's married)
Let's not get bogged down by that.

1446
00:40:01,600 --> 00:40:02,240
We already...

1447
00:40:02,880 --> 00:40:03,480
What's this?

1448
00:40:04,660 --> 00:40:05,700
(A dead memory attacks me)

1449
00:40:05,720 --> 00:40:06,480
What's this?

1450
00:40:06,480 --> 00:40:07,520
Are those shoes?

1451
00:40:09,960 --> 00:40:12,160
These seem like the shoes
that prove our relationship.

1452
00:40:12,500 --> 00:40:15,140
The young-at-heart kind of thing.

1453
00:40:16,320 --> 00:40:17,280
(Stealing every gaze)

1454
00:40:17,280 --> 00:40:18,280
(With the bright light)
The princess' glass slippers.

1455
00:40:18,300 --> 00:40:20,140
(Every step leads the trend)
How stylish.

1456
00:40:20,500 --> 00:40:22,900
You have a pair of light-up shoes?

1457
00:40:22,900 --> 00:40:23,780
A red-soled sneaker.

1458
00:40:23,920 --> 00:40:24,900
(Whose shoe is this?)

1459
00:40:25,030 --> 00:40:26,790
This belongs to my Cinderfella.

1460
00:40:26,850 --> 00:40:28,190
(Cinderfella's exclusive flashy shoe)

1461
00:40:28,190 --> 00:40:30,090
Your Cinderfella?

1462
00:40:30,510 --> 00:40:32,390
Whoever can fit into it

1463
00:40:32,390 --> 00:40:33,990
is my guy.

1464
00:40:35,320 --> 00:40:36,840
(Devoted tech mogul)
You keep looking at Zhou Keyu.

1465
00:40:37,400 --> 00:40:38,680
You want him to fit them.

1466
00:40:38,700 --> 00:40:40,050
(Talented family heir)

1467
00:40:40,170 --> 00:40:42,290
(Authoritative leader
of the detective circle)

1468
00:40:42,370 --> 00:40:44,060
(Who is her old flame?)

1469
00:40:44,080 --> 00:40:45,480
Who told me to try them on?

1470
00:40:45,500 --> 00:40:46,200
(Who is my real father?)

1471
00:40:46,240 --> 00:40:46,880
So smart.

1472
00:40:46,880 --> 00:40:48,200
Who's my dad?

1473
00:40:48,200 --> 00:40:49,260
(Cinderfella, try on the shoe!)

1474
00:40:49,280 --> 00:40:51,360
It's gotta be you. Only your age fits.

1475
00:40:53,760 --> 00:40:55,000
(Taking it off confidently)
There's me too.

1476
00:40:55,000 --> 00:40:57,880
Right. We should both
be able to fit them.

1477
00:40:57,880 --> 00:41:00,520
No, not me. My age doesn't work.

1478
00:41:00,960 --> 00:41:02,000
No, the two of us are...

1479
00:41:02,000 --> 00:41:03,160
Right. We're not the same generation.

1480
00:41:03,160 --> 00:41:04,240
(It's complicated)
I'm one generation older.

1481
00:41:04,240 --> 00:41:05,600
Right.

1482
00:41:07,820 --> 00:41:09,060
Is it yours?

1483
00:41:11,520 --> 00:41:13,040
(Perfect match)

1484
00:41:13,060 --> 00:41:14,580
It fits perfectly.

1485
00:41:15,360 --> 00:41:17,500
(Like it was custom-made)

1486
00:41:19,220 --> 00:41:20,540
You're her Cinderfella.

1487
00:41:20,600 --> 00:41:22,720
(Is An Ke the Cinderfella?)

1488
00:41:23,160 --> 00:41:24,440
(Are you my real dad?)

1489
00:41:26,560 --> 00:41:28,160
Why give him the shoes?

1490
00:41:31,040 --> 00:41:32,520
Acting shameless at your age.

1491
00:41:32,520 --> 00:41:34,520
Acting shameless at my age?

1492
00:41:36,720 --> 00:41:37,600
You were really resisting it.

1493
00:41:37,600 --> 00:41:38,480
No, that's not it.

1494
00:41:38,480 --> 00:41:41,280
Because you couldn't
be that decisive back then.

1495
00:41:41,880 --> 00:41:43,120
They can all fit them.

1496
00:41:43,900 --> 00:41:45,220
(He Jiahuan takes the lead to try it on)

1497
00:41:45,240 --> 00:41:46,920
He really went for it.
He actually tried them.

1498
00:41:47,840 --> 00:41:49,960
You're only in your twenties.
How could it be you?

1499
00:41:52,080 --> 00:41:52,920
He's trying them too.

1500
00:41:53,860 --> 00:41:55,380
(Fits just as well)

1501
00:41:55,640 --> 00:41:56,280
It's...

1502
00:41:56,280 --> 00:41:57,280
It's not really about the shoes.

1503
00:41:57,280 --> 00:41:58,280
I just want to be the dad.

1504
00:41:58,420 --> 00:41:59,100
(Elder wish +1)

1505
00:42:00,050 --> 00:42:01,130
(Ke's defense: This isn't mine)
I'm too old.

1506
00:42:01,130 --> 00:42:02,810
I can't pull off shoes this trendy.

1507
00:42:03,170 --> 00:42:04,450
What about back then?

1508
00:42:04,450 --> 00:42:06,010
23 years ago.

1509
00:42:06,010 --> 00:42:07,410
The kid was born 23 years ago.

1510
00:42:07,410 --> 00:42:08,970
Am I that embarrassing to you?

1511
00:42:08,970 --> 00:42:09,650
No.

1512
00:42:14,280 --> 00:42:16,340
K-E.

1513
00:42:16,340 --> 00:42:17,350
Wait.

1514
00:42:17,350 --> 00:42:19,400
(K-E, Ke)
Ke.

1515
00:42:19,400 --> 00:42:19,960
Ke.

1516
00:42:19,960 --> 00:42:20,610
K-E.

1517
00:42:20,610 --> 00:42:21,220
Ke.

1518
00:42:21,220 --> 00:42:22,150
(Only person related to K-E)
Call him Dad.

1519
00:42:22,150 --> 00:42:23,740
Stop playing dumb.

1520
00:42:23,880 --> 00:42:24,880
Just bow to him.

1521
00:42:25,580 --> 00:42:27,970
(Ke Daole makes a temporary comeback)
This is Ke Daole,

1522
00:42:27,970 --> 00:42:31,450
aka Dollar Ke, who exposes fakers.

1523
00:42:32,490 --> 00:42:33,030
It's you, right?

1524
00:42:33,030 --> 00:42:33,680
Ke.

1525
00:42:33,680 --> 00:42:34,070
Wait.

1526
00:42:34,070 --> 00:42:35,070
♪Miss you. You didn't reject me♪
That night...

1527
00:42:35,070 --> 00:42:35,970
♪Heart. I ended up hurting you♪
That night...

1528
00:42:35,970 --> 00:42:36,690
Ke...

1529
00:42:40,180 --> 00:42:40,820
Ke...

1530
00:42:43,520 --> 00:42:44,440
(Checking again and again)
He really doesn't want to admit it.

1531
00:42:44,910 --> 00:42:47,800
You really are Ding's biological father.

1532
00:42:47,840 --> 00:42:49,280
How are you so sure?

1533
00:42:49,280 --> 00:42:50,080
(Ding's biological father,
suspected to be An Ke)

1534
00:42:50,080 --> 00:42:51,840
Because the evidence is right here.

1535
00:42:52,440 --> 00:42:54,840
This part is already solid.

1536
00:42:54,840 --> 00:42:56,580
(Detectives can reproduce too!)
Why can't he have a detective dad?

1537
00:42:56,600 --> 00:42:58,160
Detectives can reproduce too.

1538
00:42:58,160 --> 00:43:01,540
(Detectives can reproduce too!)

1539
00:43:01,540 --> 00:43:04,530
So we're confirming this now?

1540
00:43:04,530 --> 00:43:06,040
But how can you be sure it's me?

1541
00:43:06,040 --> 00:43:07,440
- You're still denying it.
- There are tons of people in this world

1542
00:43:07,440 --> 00:43:08,420
with "Ke" in their names.

1543
00:43:08,420 --> 00:43:09,250
(Refuse to admit it)

1544
00:43:09,250 --> 00:43:10,330
Exactly, maybe it's just coincidence.

1545
00:43:10,330 --> 00:43:10,970
Forget it.

1546
00:43:10,970 --> 00:43:12,820
Let's just move on
and find the next clue.

1547
00:43:12,820 --> 00:43:14,960
Quick, let's stop talking about this.

1548
00:43:14,960 --> 00:43:15,760
This one.

1549
00:43:15,760 --> 00:43:16,470
Nothing left.

1550
00:43:17,680 --> 00:43:18,150
Nothing.

1551
00:43:18,150 --> 00:43:18,820
(Emotionally unavailable)

1552
00:43:21,190 --> 00:43:22,390
So in your heart,

1553
00:43:22,390 --> 00:43:23,220
you still don't believe this is true?

1554
00:43:23,220 --> 00:43:24,350
I know you're trying to help me.

1555
00:43:24,350 --> 00:43:25,450
Stop talking already.

1556
00:43:29,560 --> 00:43:30,720
Nicely played.

1557
00:43:37,340 --> 00:43:38,020
Wait.

1558
00:43:40,340 --> 00:43:41,300
I'm sorry.

1559
00:43:42,220 --> 00:43:43,180
I just remembered something.

1560
00:43:48,860 --> 00:43:50,340
He only remembered it now.

1561
00:43:50,340 --> 00:43:53,100
When I was younger,

1562
00:43:53,100 --> 00:43:54,220
there was indeed a period

1563
00:43:55,620 --> 00:43:56,580
where I lived wildly and recklessly.

1564
00:43:57,700 --> 00:43:59,100
I want to ask you something.

1565
00:43:59,100 --> 00:44:00,700
The perfume you use,

1566
00:44:00,700 --> 00:44:02,540
is it cedarwood

1567
00:44:02,540 --> 00:44:04,140
and moss?

1568
00:44:06,940 --> 00:44:07,980
I'm the one using it.

1569
00:44:08,980 --> 00:44:10,300
It's you?

1570
00:44:10,300 --> 00:44:10,660
Then,

1571
00:44:11,300 --> 00:44:13,260
(Emotional rollercoaster)
what kind of father are you to me now?

1572
00:44:14,900 --> 00:44:15,260
No, no.

1573
00:44:15,260 --> 00:44:16,440
(Add more dramatic effect)

1574
00:44:17,040 --> 00:44:17,960
"A Group-Buy Dad."

1575
00:44:18,900 --> 00:44:19,620
Ding is shocked.

1576
00:44:19,720 --> 00:44:21,700
(His first dad and second dad
are both his dads)

1577
00:44:21,720 --> 00:44:24,320
(New Area Unlocked: An Er's Room)
"Yellow Amnesia Love."

1578
00:44:24,320 --> 00:44:25,240
(The Yellow Amnesia Romance)
What does that mean?

1579
00:44:25,240 --> 00:44:25,960
The two of us.

1580
00:44:25,960 --> 00:44:26,960
The movie "Blue Love."

1581
00:44:26,960 --> 00:44:28,600
We're "Yellow Amnesia Love."

1582
00:44:29,500 --> 00:44:31,580
March 17th, 2016,

1583
00:44:31,580 --> 00:44:32,400
8PM.

1584
00:44:32,400 --> 00:44:33,490
I hacked into your home
surveillance system.

1585
00:44:33,520 --> 00:44:34,760
That's our theme song?

1586
00:44:34,760 --> 00:44:35,480
Yeah.

1587
00:44:35,480 --> 00:44:36,400
Yeah, we made a ton of versions

1588
00:44:36,400 --> 00:44:37,960
for the theme song this year

1589
00:44:38,320 --> 00:44:39,280
as background music

1590
00:44:39,280 --> 00:44:40,280
It's really good.

1591
00:44:41,400 --> 00:44:42,470
As for the heir issue,

1592
00:44:42,470 --> 00:44:43,810
don't even consider Jin Xiangyu anymore.

1593
00:44:43,900 --> 00:44:45,490
(Another plot twist)

1594
00:44:45,490 --> 00:44:47,000
The moment I saw her taste in men,

1595
00:44:47,350 --> 00:44:48,720
I knew she was no good.

1596
00:44:50,190 --> 00:44:52,550
Her ex-boyfriend is An Er's subordinate.

1597
00:44:52,550 --> 00:44:53,780
An Er's subordinate?

1598
00:44:53,780 --> 00:44:55,970
Yeah,
my ex-boyfriend worked under An Er.

1599
00:44:55,970 --> 00:44:56,890
Shi Wu'ai.

1600
00:44:57,470 --> 00:44:58,520
(Jin Xiangyu's ex-boyfriend: Shi Wu'ai)
According to An Er,

1601
00:44:58,520 --> 00:44:59,670
(An Er's subordinate)
that man was also involved

1602
00:44:59,670 --> 00:45:00,820
in the poisoned-glass incident
back in '92.

1603
00:45:01,420 --> 00:45:02,620
(Poisoned glass?)

1604
00:45:02,620 --> 00:45:04,420
Then he got involved with Wu,

1605
00:45:04,420 --> 00:45:05,550
did all sorts of disgraceful things,

1606
00:45:05,550 --> 00:45:06,660
and even had a child together.

1607
00:45:06,660 --> 00:45:07,370
Me?

1608
00:45:07,370 --> 00:45:08,040
Yeah, him.

1609
00:45:08,870 --> 00:45:11,050
I already showed mercy

1610
00:45:11,050 --> 00:45:12,440
by merely kicking that child
out of the An family.

1611
00:45:13,140 --> 00:45:14,140
Kicked out of the An family?

1612
00:45:15,010 --> 00:45:15,930
Then why am I still in the An family?

1613
00:45:15,930 --> 00:45:17,410
He didn't kick you out.

1614
00:45:17,850 --> 00:45:19,410
(Something's off!)
"I already showed mercy..."

1615
00:45:19,410 --> 00:45:19,960
When can they

1616
00:45:19,960 --> 00:45:21,600
finally give you a villain arc?

1617
00:45:21,600 --> 00:45:22,160
I'd love to see that.

1618
00:45:22,580 --> 00:45:24,260
(Please wait)

1619
00:45:24,260 --> 00:45:25,540
So is it possible

1620
00:45:25,540 --> 00:45:27,570
that he's not actually our child?

1621
00:45:31,600 --> 00:45:32,320
Ding is lost.

1622
00:45:32,320 --> 00:45:33,480
Ding's quest to find his dad.

1623
00:45:34,680 --> 00:45:36,480
At this point, he didn't even care
about solving the case.

1624
00:45:37,320 --> 00:45:38,200
He just wanted to find his real dad.

1625
00:45:39,980 --> 00:45:41,500
(That's right. It's just that magical)

1626
00:45:41,620 --> 00:45:42,740
(Absolutely explosive)

1627
00:45:44,580 --> 00:45:45,720
(But Uncle Er's bed finally gave out)

1628
00:45:45,740 --> 00:45:46,350
Wait.

1629
00:45:46,880 --> 00:45:47,880
What the heck?

1630
00:45:48,040 --> 00:45:48,360
Turns out

1631
00:45:48,360 --> 00:45:50,600
(Mystery solved)
it collapsed when you sat down.

1632
00:45:51,080 --> 00:45:52,000
That scared me.

1633
00:45:52,580 --> 00:45:54,540
(He's totally bewildered)
Is there some kind of hidden mechanism?

1634
00:45:54,560 --> 00:45:55,920
A hidden mechanism.

1635
00:45:55,920 --> 00:45:56,480
It literally just...

1636
00:45:56,480 --> 00:45:57,490
(Wild theory)
Collapsed from sitting on it.

1637
00:45:57,490 --> 00:45:58,370
It simply couldn't handle

1638
00:45:58,370 --> 00:45:59,430
the weight of three grown men.

1639
00:45:59,430 --> 00:46:00,820
Just straight-up collapsed.

1640
00:46:00,820 --> 00:46:01,460
Right.

1641
00:46:02,150 --> 00:46:03,550
"I'll send the rest
to your email later."

1642
00:46:04,480 --> 00:46:05,100
Email?

1643
00:46:05,100 --> 00:46:06,140
Go check if there's email access.

1644
00:46:06,140 --> 00:46:06,910
See if there's email.

1645
00:46:07,650 --> 00:46:08,560
Then there should be a computer.

1646
00:46:09,500 --> 00:46:10,480
Probably something computer-related.

1647
00:46:10,480 --> 00:46:11,130
Nothing here.

1648
00:46:11,820 --> 00:46:12,140
Drawers.

1649
00:46:12,140 --> 00:46:12,620
Check the drawers.

1650
00:46:14,620 --> 00:46:15,940
Drawer.

1651
00:46:17,540 --> 00:46:18,420
There's a laptop here.

1652
00:46:21,380 --> 00:46:23,270
Back then, that woman Ning got pregnant.

1653
00:46:24,100 --> 00:46:25,580
That woman Ning?

1654
00:46:26,160 --> 00:46:27,020
(My woman?)

1655
00:46:27,020 --> 00:46:28,580
You had a woman back then?

1656
00:46:28,580 --> 00:46:29,660
Keep reading.

1657
00:46:29,660 --> 00:46:31,140
That woman Ning got pregnant.

1658
00:46:31,140 --> 00:46:32,820
She was only one of Er's subordinates.

1659
00:46:32,820 --> 00:46:33,900
But Er said

1660
00:46:33,900 --> 00:46:35,340
she was also involved

1661
00:46:35,340 --> 00:46:36,980
in the 1992 poisoned-glass incident.

1662
00:46:37,200 --> 00:46:38,540
(Ning's woman was involved
in the poisoned-glass case?)

1663
00:46:38,540 --> 00:46:40,780
I never expected she secretly
got pregnant with Ning's child.

1664
00:46:41,020 --> 00:46:41,420
(I had a child too?)

1665
00:46:41,460 --> 00:46:44,140
Coincidentally, Jin Xiangyu
also gave birth to that fatherless child.

1666
00:46:44,240 --> 00:46:45,920
(He called me fatherless)

1667
00:46:45,940 --> 00:46:48,140
Didn't she cuckold me?

1668
00:46:48,140 --> 00:46:50,140
Then I'll make her raise my grandson.

1669
00:46:50,820 --> 00:46:53,220
You're his grandson.

1670
00:46:53,800 --> 00:46:56,040
(An Xiaoning and An Xiaoding
are father and son?)

1671
