1996.

2208
01:01:06,840 --> 01:01:08,640
(1996)

2209
01:01:08,900 --> 01:01:09,340
What?

2210
01:01:18,500 --> 01:01:20,260
The current date

2211
01:01:21,260 --> 01:01:22,460
is 1996.

2212
01:01:28,860 --> 01:01:29,740
(Oh my)

2213
01:01:31,180 --> 01:01:33,340
(Oh)

2214
01:01:34,340 --> 01:01:35,020
(Oh my)

2215
01:01:38,880 --> 01:01:39,480
A time shift.

2216
01:01:39,480 --> 01:01:40,340
(Oh my)

2217
01:01:42,300 --> 01:01:44,700
(That was impressive)

2218
01:01:44,720 --> 01:01:45,280
A magical portal.

2219
01:01:45,880 --> 01:01:48,080
(An Songqiu)
See? He can even control the weather.

2220
01:01:49,900 --> 01:01:51,380
However, a major problem has arisen,

2221
01:01:51,380 --> 01:01:52,500
and we need everyone's help.

2222
01:01:53,700 --> 01:01:55,340
The groom has an urgent
matter to attend to.

2223
01:01:55,340 --> 01:01:56,700
So we need someone to take his place?

2224
01:01:56,700 --> 01:01:57,260
No way.

2225
01:02:01,380 --> 01:02:02,100
That is correct.

2226
01:02:02,460 --> 01:02:03,580
Are you serious?

2227
01:02:04,160 --> 01:02:05,100
This is absurd.

2228
01:02:05,110 --> 01:02:06,140
Then what about your Xi Hu?

2229
01:02:06,280 --> 01:02:07,180
(Xi Hu, let me explain)

2230
01:02:07,180 --> 01:02:08,460
It is fine. It is only a substitute.

2231
01:02:08,460 --> 01:02:10,100
You'll only be the groom
during the rehearsal.

2232
01:02:10,500 --> 01:02:12,140
Who will take the groom's place?

2233
01:02:12,140 --> 01:02:13,980
I have four younger brothers here.

2234
01:02:13,980 --> 01:02:15,100
Which one do you prefer?

2235
01:02:17,360 --> 01:02:17,840
(Side quest)

2236
01:02:17,840 --> 01:02:18,280
(Side quest activated)

2237
01:02:18,280 --> 01:02:19,040
(Please help the butler
complete the wedding rehearsal)

2238
01:02:19,040 --> 01:02:20,080
(Please choose a substitute
groom for An San)

2239
01:02:21,300 --> 01:02:22,060
Do I get to choose?

2240
01:02:22,060 --> 01:02:22,900
My choice doesn't matter.

2241
01:02:22,900 --> 01:02:24,220
(Almost got selected)
Everyone has to volunteer,

2242
01:02:24,220 --> 01:02:24,740
alright?

2243
01:02:24,740 --> 01:02:26,140
The four of you, gather together.

2244
01:02:26,140 --> 01:02:28,040
(Crunch)
We'll settle with rock-paper-scissors.

2245
01:02:28,060 --> 01:02:28,660
Okay.

2246
01:02:28,660 --> 01:02:29,420
(Fair and impartial)
Very well.

2247
01:02:29,420 --> 01:02:29,950
Let fate decide.

2248
01:02:29,950 --> 01:02:31,220
This is called destiny.

2249
01:02:31,220 --> 01:02:31,980
Destined.

2250
01:02:32,760 --> 01:02:34,040
Destined for a pig's backside.

2251
01:02:35,200 --> 01:02:36,360
Destined for a pig's backside.

2252
01:02:37,680 --> 01:02:38,720
(Loses eligibility to compete)
Destined for a pig's backside.

2253
01:02:39,060 --> 01:02:39,860
Rock-paper-scissors.

2254
01:02:39,880 --> 01:02:41,160
(Fist, Paper)

2255
01:02:41,760 --> 01:02:42,160
(That is not right)

2256
01:02:42,160 --> 01:02:42,740
(Wait a moment)
You go.

2257
01:02:43,420 --> 01:02:43,740
You won.

2258
01:02:43,740 --> 01:02:44,780
(What are you celebrating?)

2259
01:02:44,840 --> 01:02:45,710
First,

2260
01:02:45,710 --> 01:02:46,720
he should complete a solo task.

2261
01:02:46,720 --> 01:02:48,160
(Kindness mode offline)
Fetch the bride from the bridal chamber.

2262
01:02:50,040 --> 01:02:51,480
That is outrageous.

2263
01:02:51,480 --> 01:02:52,500
(Urgently seeking a bridesmaid,
any gender)

2264
01:02:52,500 --> 01:02:53,280
He really is ruthless.

2265
01:02:53,280 --> 01:02:55,120
He wants to do it this way.
Did you hear that?

2266
01:02:55,320 --> 01:02:55,920
No.

2267
01:02:55,920 --> 01:02:56,800
(Quick-thinking as always)
Okay, next,

2268
01:02:56,800 --> 01:02:58,040
(Competing for the role)
you will head alone to...

2269
01:02:58,920 --> 01:03:00,080
I am getting too old for this.

2270
01:03:00,080 --> 01:03:01,200
(Scissors, Fist)
A dark place.

2271
01:03:01,200 --> 01:03:01,820
(The groom watches from the sidelines)

2272
01:03:01,820 --> 01:03:01,980
(Bridesmaid selection begins)

2273
01:03:02,980 --> 01:03:03,900
No way.

2274
01:03:03,900 --> 01:03:04,570
Wait.

2275
01:03:04,600 --> 01:03:05,200
No way.

2276
01:03:05,620 --> 01:03:06,740
I'm at that age.

2277
01:03:06,740 --> 01:03:07,000
Come on.

2278
01:03:07,000 --> 01:03:07,590
It's alright, Ning.

2279
01:03:07,590 --> 01:03:08,960
Keep saying that, and it'll happen.

2280
01:03:09,140 --> 01:03:09,860
I can do it.

2281
01:03:09,860 --> 01:03:10,680
(Tolerant)
It is fine.

2282
01:03:10,820 --> 01:03:11,340
No.

2283
01:03:11,340 --> 01:03:11,740
Wait.

2284
01:03:13,700 --> 01:03:14,080
(As if it has your name on it)

2285
01:03:14,080 --> 01:03:15,500
That purple dress looks
made for you, Ning.

2286
01:03:15,500 --> 01:03:16,720
(Are you serious?)

2287
01:03:17,000 --> 01:03:18,560
(A vintage purple sequined gown)

2288
01:03:19,720 --> 01:03:21,000
It's less dramatic once it's on.

2289
01:03:21,000 --> 01:03:22,400
It looks beautiful on you.

2290
01:03:22,460 --> 01:03:24,100
(A masterpiece)
It really complements your complexion.

2291
01:03:24,400 --> 01:03:25,300
It looks wonderful.

2292
01:03:25,300 --> 01:03:26,380
(The shy groom)

2293
01:03:26,380 --> 01:03:27,580
(The assertive bridesmaid)

2294
01:03:27,600 --> 01:03:29,440
Ning, this is too funny.

2295
01:03:29,440 --> 01:03:32,460
(The aloof best man)

2296
01:03:35,960 --> 01:03:37,760
That outfit looks amazing on you.

2297
01:03:37,760 --> 01:03:38,960
I really like this one.

2298
01:03:40,740 --> 01:03:41,060
(An Er, the discounted version)

2299
01:03:41,080 --> 01:03:42,840
Yes, like an oil prince.

2300
01:03:42,840 --> 01:03:43,260
(Isn't that someone we know?)

2301
01:03:43,600 --> 01:03:43,920
Yes.

2302
01:03:45,360 --> 01:03:47,280
You could genuinely
use this look for a concert.

2303
01:03:50,620 --> 01:03:53,660
(Chewing)

2304
01:03:53,820 --> 01:03:54,580
You are right.

2305
01:03:54,580 --> 01:03:55,980
Is that not all of you?

2306
01:03:56,780 --> 01:03:59,020
Could the one you
are holding be An Xiaowen?

2307
01:04:01,820 --> 01:04:03,100
An Xiaoding.

2308
01:04:03,740 --> 01:04:05,660
Ms. Wen.

2309
01:04:06,180 --> 01:04:06,580
Ms. Wen.

2310
01:04:06,580 --> 01:04:07,780
Wen.

2311
01:04:08,940 --> 01:04:10,620
You are so beautiful.

2312
01:04:10,620 --> 01:04:12,300
I want to be as beautiful
as you when I grow up.

2313
01:04:12,300 --> 01:04:14,380
Do you want to look like
me when you grow up?

2314
01:04:14,380 --> 01:04:17,100
You will be even more beautiful
than I am.

2315
01:04:17,100 --> 01:04:18,780
Mr. He.

2316
01:04:19,820 --> 01:04:20,660
Hello.

2317
01:04:20,660 --> 01:04:21,860
Hello. You are so handsome.

2318
01:04:21,860 --> 01:04:22,460
You too.

2319
01:04:22,460 --> 01:04:23,620
I want to be as handsome as you.

2320
01:04:24,180 --> 01:04:24,780
You will.

2321
01:04:24,780 --> 01:04:25,740
You'll be even more handsome.

2322
01:04:25,740 --> 01:04:28,580
Mr. Ding.

2323
01:04:28,580 --> 01:04:29,700
Is that Ding?

2324
01:04:29,720 --> 01:04:31,520
Why did Mr. Ding go over to you?

2325
01:04:31,520 --> 01:04:32,760
(Mr. Ding is not an insider)
How would I know?

2326
01:04:33,960 --> 01:04:35,160
He went to the wrong person.

2327
01:04:35,160 --> 01:04:36,000
(A prophet)

2328
01:04:36,000 --> 01:04:37,720
He said, "I want to be as handsome
as you."

2329
01:04:37,720 --> 01:04:39,680
I want to be as handsome as you.

2330
01:04:39,680 --> 01:04:41,000
So he walked over to you.

2331
01:04:41,440 --> 01:04:43,000
(I'm your future self)
He should've come to me.

2332
01:04:43,000 --> 01:04:44,840
He will.

2333
01:04:45,640 --> 01:04:47,160
He really did go to the wrong person.

2334
01:04:47,860 --> 01:04:48,460
(I like hearing that)

2335
01:04:49,060 --> 01:04:51,540
At this joyful moment, our groom

2336
01:04:52,060 --> 01:04:52,880
(Tearing up)
has been moved to tears.

2337
01:04:52,880 --> 01:04:53,840
What is wrong?

2338
01:04:54,520 --> 01:04:55,200
Touched?

2339
01:04:56,040 --> 01:04:56,720
I am truly touched.

2340
01:04:56,720 --> 01:04:58,640
I hardly dared to move.
I was too overwhelmed.

2341
01:04:59,220 --> 01:05:01,020
My nephew and niece are here.

2342
01:05:01,080 --> 01:05:02,080
(My sister-in-law, niece, and nephew)
Why didn't you mention me?

2343
01:05:02,080 --> 01:05:03,040
You are an outsider.

2344
01:05:03,260 --> 01:05:04,700
(A harsh truth)

2345
01:05:04,700 --> 01:05:06,510
With all of you here as witnesses,

2346
01:05:08,050 --> 01:05:09,440
I shall walk toward
my final destination.

2347
01:05:09,440 --> 01:05:10,820
(Unable to look directly)

2348
01:05:11,680 --> 01:05:12,840
That sends chills down my spine.

2349
01:05:14,800 --> 01:05:16,070
What?

2350
01:05:16,260 --> 01:05:17,280
The way that sounded

2351
01:05:17,280 --> 01:05:18,200
was rather unsettling.

2352
01:05:18,340 --> 01:05:20,200
(I have a bad feeling about this)

2353
01:05:20,240 --> 01:05:21,760
Look how frightened Ding is.

2354
01:05:25,320 --> 01:05:26,280
Ding.

2355
01:05:29,320 --> 01:05:30,680
That was actually quite terrifying.

2356
01:05:31,320 --> 01:05:32,560
It really was.

2357
01:05:34,220 --> 01:05:35,340
(Regularly traumatized)

2358
01:05:37,510 --> 01:05:38,390
She...

2359
01:05:38,390 --> 01:05:39,930
There is blood coming from her mouth.

2360
01:05:40,240 --> 01:05:41,430
She is coughing up blood.

2361
01:05:41,430 --> 01:05:42,640
It is alright.

2362
01:05:44,450 --> 01:05:45,870
A puppet.

2363
01:05:47,900 --> 01:05:49,130
It is a puppet.

2364
01:05:49,130 --> 01:05:50,200
It has appeared.

2365
01:05:52,700 --> 01:05:55,300
(A pained expression)

2366
01:05:55,300 --> 01:05:56,460
(Offering reassurance)

2367
01:05:58,100 --> 01:06:00,020
(The An family's curse has come true)

2368
01:06:00,460 --> 01:06:01,570
I have to sleep tonight.

2369
01:06:02,440 --> 01:06:03,660
Have to sleep tonight.

2370
01:06:03,940 --> 01:06:04,580
(Hall lights up)

2371
01:06:11,020 --> 01:06:12,860
(What is happening?)

2372
01:06:13,280 --> 01:06:14,280
You startled me.

2373
01:06:14,280 --> 01:06:16,700
The bridesmaid has taken the groom away.

2374
01:06:16,700 --> 01:06:17,180
(The bridesmaid steals the groom)

2375
01:06:17,540 --> 01:06:19,860
(The runaway groom's
formidable bridesmaid)

2376
01:06:19,860 --> 01:06:21,180
What is going on?

2377
01:06:21,180 --> 01:06:23,060
Everyone, please remain quiet.

2378
01:06:23,360 --> 01:06:24,770
I never expected

2379
01:06:24,770 --> 01:06:26,150
such an accident to happen today.

2380
01:06:26,660 --> 01:06:27,660
Who could have predicted this?

2381
01:06:28,320 --> 01:06:29,480
Who could have predicted this?

2382
01:06:30,080 --> 01:06:31,280
Don't say something so ridiculous

2383
01:06:31,280 --> 01:06:32,600
with such a serious expression.

2384
01:06:32,600 --> 01:06:33,720
We should leave immediately.

2385
01:06:33,720 --> 01:06:34,470
Why are we leaving?

2386
01:06:34,470 --> 01:06:35,320
Why?

2387
01:06:35,320 --> 01:06:36,340
Leave now.

2388
01:06:36,340 --> 01:06:37,050
What happened?

2389
01:06:37,050 --> 01:06:38,440
The ring has not been delivered yet.

2390
01:06:38,940 --> 01:06:40,180
(That is certainly worrying)

2391
01:06:40,180 --> 01:06:41,740
(Everyone leaves)

2392
01:06:41,740 --> 01:06:43,330
Why do we have to leave?

2393
01:06:44,860 --> 01:06:45,580
(An Songqiu leaves the scene)

2394
01:06:45,600 --> 01:06:46,400
They just left us here.

2395
01:06:46,400 --> 01:06:47,400
They abandoned us here.

2396
01:06:47,660 --> 01:06:48,540
(The banquet has not even begun yet)

2397
01:06:48,540 --> 01:06:50,550
We were only substitutes to begin with.

2398
01:06:50,550 --> 01:06:51,630
You're too deep in the role.

2399
01:06:51,890 --> 01:06:52,280
You can't go.

2400
01:06:52,280 --> 01:06:53,540
(Got him)
Am I not allowed to leave?

2401
01:06:53,540 --> 01:06:53,940
No.

2402
01:06:53,960 --> 01:06:54,660
Where did he go?

2403
01:06:54,660 --> 01:06:56,300
It suddenly disappeared after the bride

2404
01:06:56,300 --> 01:06:56,940
collapsed.

2405
01:06:56,940 --> 01:06:57,540
I also don't know.

2406
01:06:57,540 --> 01:06:59,100
It wasn't my fault, was it?

2407
01:06:59,500 --> 01:07:00,060
Not your concern.

2408
01:07:00,060 --> 01:07:01,140
Then I will give this ring to you

2409
01:07:01,140 --> 01:07:01,860
as an apology.

2410
01:07:01,860 --> 01:07:02,720
(At least the trip was not wasted)

2411
01:07:03,500 --> 01:07:04,300
I cannot accept it.

2412
01:07:04,300 --> 01:07:04,900
(Still has principles)
Oh, cannot?

2413
01:07:05,140 --> 01:07:06,820
You actually have strong principles.

2414
01:07:07,020 --> 01:07:08,600
By the way, Chongqing
wontons are delicious.

2415
01:07:08,600 --> 01:07:09,260
(Amused by his own joke)
Really?

2416
01:07:09,260 --> 01:07:10,700
(Genuinely hungry)
I will make sure to try them next time.

2417
01:07:10,980 --> 01:07:12,340
When those kids grow up and marry,

2418
01:07:12,340 --> 01:07:13,660
they will all come to you.

2419
01:07:14,380 --> 01:07:15,460
Fine. They can all come to me.

2420
01:07:15,460 --> 01:07:16,420
(Task completed)
They will all come to you.

2421
01:07:16,420 --> 01:07:17,500
(The bride has disappeared version)
I need to leave now.

2422
01:07:17,500 --> 01:07:18,220
Don't lose that item.

2423
01:07:18,220 --> 01:07:19,360
They'll come looking for you later.

2424
01:07:20,180 --> 01:07:21,100
Looking for me?

2425
01:07:22,340 --> 01:07:23,860
Just don't lose it.

2426
01:07:24,280 --> 01:07:24,780
(Fearless)

2427
01:07:24,780 --> 01:07:25,940
She will come looking for you.

2428
01:07:27,140 --> 01:07:28,340
Is this ring really fine?

2429
01:07:28,340 --> 01:07:28,700
Take it.

2430
01:07:28,700 --> 01:07:29,900
(Still a little frightened)
The bride will come looking for you.

2431
01:07:29,900 --> 01:07:30,460
Hold on to it.

2432
01:07:30,820 --> 01:07:31,380
That's scary.

2433
01:07:31,920 --> 01:07:33,000
Ding, that was terrifying.

2434
01:07:33,260 --> 01:07:33,820
(Frightened)

2435
01:07:34,080 --> 01:07:35,880
Our show actually looks quite good.

2436
01:07:35,880 --> 01:07:36,760
It was pretty scary.

2437
01:07:37,480 --> 01:07:38,520
Was it?

2438
01:07:38,520 --> 01:07:39,960
No, objectively speaking,

2439
01:07:39,960 --> 01:07:40,960
did you find it frightening?

2440
01:07:40,960 --> 01:07:41,720
I did too.

2441
01:07:41,720 --> 01:07:43,240
Yes, it was quite terrifying.

2442
01:07:43,960 --> 01:07:44,600
(It gets scarier the more
I think about it)

2443
01:07:44,600 --> 01:07:45,640
When that door opened earlier,

2444
01:07:45,640 --> 01:07:46,560
it was truly frightening.

2445
01:07:47,000 --> 01:07:48,400
So, are we still playing games tonight?

2446
01:07:49,160 --> 01:07:50,880
No, there is no time for games tonight.

2447
01:07:51,480 --> 01:07:52,200
When it is loading

2448
01:07:52,200 --> 01:07:52,960
and the screen goes black,

2449
01:07:52,960 --> 01:07:54,080
what if you suddenly see...

2450
01:07:54,080 --> 01:07:54,960
Right, during the blackout,

2451
01:07:54,960 --> 01:07:56,800
there is another face behind your
own, staring at you.

2452
01:07:57,420 --> 01:07:59,660
(Quits gaming for ten seconds)

2453
01:07:59,680 --> 01:08:00,600
He would go to bed early.

2454
01:08:00,600 --> 01:08:01,320
He's terrified.

2455
01:08:02,440 --> 01:08:03,560
That completely overwhelmed me.

2456
01:08:04,280 --> 01:08:05,480
Actually, before the vote that day,

2457
01:08:05,480 --> 01:08:06,840
I was extremely conflicted.

2458
01:08:07,800 --> 01:08:08,880
It was between the two of us.

2459
01:08:08,880 --> 01:08:10,480
To me, it was simply...

2460
01:08:10,480 --> 01:08:10,960
Well...

2461
01:08:11,160 --> 01:08:12,080
Do you know what I thought then?

2462
01:08:12,080 --> 01:08:13,640
I thought it was one
of your new tactics.

2463
01:08:14,120 --> 01:08:16,390
I thought, Ning is incredible.

2464
01:08:17,120 --> 01:08:17,520
I felt

2465
01:08:17,520 --> 01:08:18,800
that it was some kind of strategy,

2466
01:08:18,800 --> 01:08:20,310
rather than your genuine sincerity.

2467
01:08:20,310 --> 01:08:21,000
Yes.

2468
01:08:21,000 --> 01:08:21,920
See? You didn't believe me.

2469
01:08:21,920 --> 01:08:23,270
That's what happens
when you overthink people.

2470
01:08:23,270 --> 01:08:24,350
I really did overthink it.

2471
01:08:24,350 --> 01:08:25,240
For me that day,

2472
01:08:25,240 --> 01:08:26,000
I felt

2473
01:08:26,000 --> 01:08:26,680
that after

2474
01:08:26,680 --> 01:08:27,680
everything was locked in,

2475
01:08:27,680 --> 01:08:29,200
the two of us
became the most suspicious.

2476
01:08:29,720 --> 01:08:30,160
Right?

2477
01:08:30,160 --> 01:08:31,120
You were tied together.

2478
01:08:31,120 --> 01:08:32,520
Both of you were called over.

2479
01:08:32,800 --> 01:08:34,600
And I was the one
who called Ding over as well.

2480
01:08:34,600 --> 01:08:36,000
But I knew it was not me.

2481
01:08:36,270 --> 01:08:37,000
So it had to be him.

2482
01:08:37,640 --> 01:08:38,880
I was thinking,

2483
01:08:38,880 --> 01:08:39,960
could it really be that simple?

2484
01:08:39,960 --> 01:08:40,760
But it was that simple.

2485
01:08:40,760 --> 01:08:42,080
It's that simple.

2486
01:08:43,160 --> 01:08:44,350
However, I understood later.

2487
01:08:44,350 --> 01:08:46,390
From my perspective, it was simple.

2488
01:08:46,390 --> 01:08:47,520
Yes, because you knew.

2489
01:08:47,520 --> 01:08:48,600
Yes, I knew it was not me.

2490
01:08:48,600 --> 01:08:49,040
Exactly.

2491
01:08:49,040 --> 01:08:49,430
Right?

2492
01:08:49,720 --> 01:08:51,840
When everyone cornered

2493
01:08:51,840 --> 01:08:52,920
you at the end,

2494
01:08:52,920 --> 01:08:53,960
how did that feel?

2495
01:08:54,430 --> 01:08:56,200
I really enjoyed

2496
01:08:56,200 --> 01:08:57,920
everyone's enthusiasm.

2497
01:08:57,920 --> 01:08:59,800
(World is cruel, yet I stay cheerful)
Yes, I genuinely enjoyed it.

2498
01:08:59,800 --> 01:09:00,520
Yes.

2499
01:09:00,520 --> 01:09:01,680
Everyone was attacking him.

2500
01:09:02,120 --> 01:09:03,160
He was almost overwhelmed.

2501
01:09:03,160 --> 01:09:04,760
But I think you handled it very well.

2502
01:09:04,760 --> 01:09:05,760
Nothing else I could do.

2503
01:09:05,760 --> 01:09:07,270
(Life punches me, I answer with paper.)
I couldn't say I'd had enough.

2504
01:09:07,270 --> 01:09:07,920
I quit.

2505
01:09:07,920 --> 01:09:08,470
Just vote for me.

2506
01:09:09,040 --> 01:09:10,240
Yes. That is true.

2507
01:09:10,640 --> 01:09:12,040
Do you think anyone this season

2508
01:09:12,040 --> 01:09:14,160
will be able to find
the crucial evidence?

2509
01:09:14,160 --> 01:09:15,800
Players, please do your best.

2510
01:09:16,200 --> 01:09:17,080
If someone does find it,

2511
01:09:17,080 --> 01:09:18,270
what reward

2512
01:09:18,270 --> 01:09:19,000
will they receive?

2513
01:09:20,840 --> 01:09:23,240
The system has unlocked
the Wish Pool feature.

2514
01:09:23,240 --> 01:09:24,390
Players may make a wish.

2515
01:09:24,390 --> 01:09:26,040
If I find the crucial evidence,

2516
01:09:26,140 --> 01:09:26,920
Let Ding Chengxin get...

2517
01:09:26,920 --> 01:09:27,660
(Confidential)

2518
01:09:27,720 --> 01:09:29,240
That only hurts others
without benefiting you.

2519
01:09:29,430 --> 01:09:30,470
I have the right

2520
01:09:30,470 --> 01:09:31,520
to designate one person...

2521
01:09:31,520 --> 01:09:32,540
(Confidential)

2522
01:09:33,920 --> 01:09:35,200
Look at Ding's expression.

2523
01:09:35,350 --> 01:09:36,430
That is clearly aimed at me.

2524
01:09:36,430 --> 01:09:37,840
I'll be unable to tell
who my teammates are.

2525
01:09:39,640 --> 01:09:40,560
Then the other guests

2526
01:09:40,560 --> 01:09:41,350
must post on Weibo...

2527
01:09:41,350 --> 01:09:42,270
(Confidential)

2528
01:09:42,270 --> 01:09:43,430
The other guests must host

2529
01:09:43,430 --> 01:09:44,350
a two-minute livestream...

2530
01:09:44,350 --> 01:09:45,180
(Confidential)

2531
01:09:46,600 --> 01:09:47,720
(That would be satisfying)
It would become the highlight.

2532
01:09:49,380 --> 01:09:51,500
(A full reveal of everyone's wishes
is about to be unlocked)

2533
01:09:51,500 --> 01:10:05,380
(Ghost Stories of Tui City Control Room)

2534
01:10:06,000 --> 01:10:06,600
(Preview of the next episode)
So beautiful.

2535
01:10:06,600 --> 01:10:08,240
Why are all of our
comments so superficial?

2536
01:10:08,240 --> 01:10:09,280
What's wrong with your lower back?

2537
01:10:09,280 --> 01:10:10,200
Scoliosis.

2538
01:10:11,260 --> 01:10:13,060
(Ning Bubble)

2539
01:10:13,060 --> 01:10:13,940
(He Yiwei)

2540
01:10:15,480 --> 01:10:16,400
You worked together before?

2541
01:10:16,400 --> 01:10:17,280
Who are you referring to?

2542
01:10:17,600 --> 01:10:19,440
Have you not acted
in a drama together before?

2543
01:10:19,440 --> 01:10:20,400
He has forgotten.

2544
01:10:21,800 --> 01:10:24,040
He kept encouraging us to eat.

2545
01:10:24,040 --> 01:10:26,400
Zhang Linghe kept telling us to eat.

2546
01:10:26,400 --> 01:10:27,720
By the time the wall came down,

2547
01:10:27,720 --> 01:10:28,800
I was full I felt like throwing up.

2548
01:10:28,800 --> 01:10:30,280
Why have I been eating this entire time?

2549
01:10:30,280 --> 01:10:31,280
Don't talk to me.

2550
01:10:31,280 --> 01:10:32,480
Why do you talk so much?

2551
01:10:33,600 --> 01:10:35,520
Are you able to tolerate
this kind of thing more easily?

2552
01:10:35,520 --> 01:10:36,680
It's more of a mental challenge.

2553
01:10:36,680 --> 01:10:37,200
No.

2554
01:10:37,200 --> 01:10:37,800
Don't worry.

2555
01:10:37,800 --> 01:10:39,400
Now that you said that,
they won't arrange it for you.

2556
01:10:39,400 --> 01:10:40,080
They definitely will,

2557
01:10:40,080 --> 01:10:40,800
that's what you fear.

2558
01:10:40,800 --> 01:10:41,920
Challenge that tests your limits.

2559
01:10:41,920 --> 01:10:43,560
It's fine. I'll bring
glutinous rice later.

2560
01:10:43,560 --> 01:10:44,840
Glutinous rice?

2561
01:10:45,400 --> 01:10:46,480
Is that what I am talking about?

2562
01:10:46,480 --> 01:10:47,480
That is far too timid.

2563
01:10:47,480 --> 01:10:48,640
(90% resemblance)
You really do look like that dog.

2564
01:10:48,640 --> 01:10:49,880
She looks like a husky.

2565
01:10:52,680 --> 01:10:54,600
It has to be Ding.

2566
01:10:54,600 --> 01:10:56,000
(NO WAY)
Ding is incredibly strong.

2567
01:10:56,000 --> 01:10:57,160
Seriously.

2568
01:10:57,160 --> 01:10:57,920
Only one chance.

2569
01:10:57,920 --> 01:10:58,480
I have no choice.

2570
01:10:58,480 --> 01:10:59,360
I am extremely afraid.

2571
01:11:02,860 --> 01:11:04,900
(Data retrieval complete)

2572
01:11:04,920 --> 01:11:06,360
Have we discovered a bug in the system?

2573
01:11:55,220 --> 01:11:59,220
♪Come now, players all,
let the game of reason start♪

2574
01:11:59,220 --> 01:12:03,660
♪Unlock each hidden trial,
let courage spark the dark♪

2575
01:12:05,680 --> 01:12:09,840
♪Night falls slow, shadows grow,
the sleuth is lost inside the maze♪

2576
01:12:09,840 --> 01:12:14,060
♪Figures pass, lanterns sparse,
dark currents drift without a trace♪

2577
01:12:14,060 --> 01:12:17,830
♪Wind picks up, footsteps rush,
cold laughter swallowed by the dark♪

2578
01:12:17,830 --> 01:12:21,940
♪Truth concealed, the night
stands still, and nothing leaves a mark♪

2579
01:12:22,120 --> 01:12:26,240
♪An unsigned letter, coded words,
the solvers gather one by one♪

2580
01:12:26,240 --> 01:12:30,350
♪A broken game, illusion reigns,
who's hiding what they've done?♪

2581
01:12:30,350 --> 01:12:33,990
♪Hushed voices, nerves on edge,
wrapped in smoke and mirrors still♪

2582
01:12:33,990 --> 01:12:36,120
♪The next second, deeper riddles,
or the answer to the kill♪

2583
01:12:36,120 --> 01:12:40,070
♪Every piece of truth
has finally come to light♪

2584
01:12:40,310 --> 01:12:44,230
♪Unlock the mystery, turn the question,
let's begin tonight♪

2585
01:12:44,440 --> 01:12:48,590
♪Side by side, no holding back,
follow every clue to find the truth♪

2586
01:12:48,590 --> 01:12:52,150
♪The story blurs like flowers in fog,
let's begin tonight♪

2587
01:12:52,410 --> 01:12:57,060
♪Search for the vanished cipher,
trace the proof, and face the sleuth♪
